# REST API -- HTTP Examples
#
# Development: server listens on http://localhost:5000 (no cert configured).
# With cert: https://localhost:8081
#
# Compatible with the VS Code REST Client extension.
# Start the server first: cd src && dotnet run --project Credfeto.Defi.Server

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

# -- 1. Health check ----------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/ping

###

# -- 2. Get available pool types ----------------------------------------------
# Returns the list of all supported pool type identifiers and their metadata.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/pools

###

# -- 3. Get ETH / liquid staking pools ----------------------------------------
# Returns enriched pool data for ETH and liquid staking tokens (e.g. stETH, rETH).
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/pools/ETH

###

# -- 4. Get stablecoin pools --------------------------------------------------
# Returns enriched pool data for stablecoin pairs (e.g. USDC, USDT, DAI).
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/pools/STABLES

###

# -- 5. Get high-yield pools --------------------------------------------------
# Returns enriched pool data for pools with elevated APY.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/pools/HIGH_YIELD

###

# -- 6. Get low-TVL pools -----------------------------------------------------
# Returns enriched pool data for pools with lower total value locked.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/pools/LOW_TVL

###

# -- 7. Get blue-chip pools ---------------------------------------------------
# Returns enriched pool data for established, high-TVL blue-chip protocols.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/pools/BLUE_CHIP
